President Trump has announced his intent to nominate Ron A. Bloom and Roman Martinez IV to the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service. Bloom's term would expire on December 8, 2020, while Martinez's term would expire on December 8, 2024. Additionally, William Shaw McDermott is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the Metropolitan Washington Airports Authority for a term ending on May 30, 2024.